# Luna OS — gaming package list
# config/package-lists/gaming.list.chroot
#
# Lutris is NOT in Debian's own repos, so it's installed via Flatpak
# (Flathub) by a build hook instead — still under its real name/branding,
# no rebranding/disguising of third-party software.

## Performance daemons
gamemode
mangohud

## Retro emulation (RetroArch + libretro cores actually packaged in Debian)
retroarch
libretro-core-info
retroarch-assets
libretro-nestopia
libretro-mgba
libretro-beetle-psx

## Windows compatibility layer (minimal Wine — not full Proton GE)
wine64
wine32:i386

## Controller support (xpad is already in-kernel; no separate dkms package
## needed — these just add userspace joystick test/config tools)
joystick
jstest-gtk

## Memory management
zram-tools
